gzip.description:
data is treated as a byte string (one M character per byte).
Sets $ECODE=,U-STDCOMPRESS-BAD-LEVEL, if level outside 1..9;
,U-STDCOMPRESS-CALLOUT-MISSING, if the .so is unloaded;
,U-STDCOMPRESS-LIBZ-FAIL, on libz failure.
Example: do gzip^STDCOMPRESS("hello",.buf)

add.description:
Calendar arithmetic for Y/M (with day-clamp on shorter months);
raw day arithmetic for W/D; second-arithmetic for H/M/S.
Example: write $$add^STDDATE("47117,0","P1DT2H30M")  ; "47118,9000"

readBytes.description:
Preserves every byte exactly. For text I/O with newline-joining
and CRLF normalisation, prefer $$readFile^STDFS instead.
Sets $ECODE=,U-STDFS-NOT-WIRED, when stdfs.so is unavailable;
,U-STDFS-OPEN-FAIL, on open(2) failure;
,U-STDFS-READ-TRUNCATED, if file exceeds the 16 MiB buffer cap.
Example: set blob=$$readBytes^STDFS("/tmp/blob.bin")

parseArray.description:
Internal ‚Äî handles empty array, comma-separated elements;
trailing comma is rejected (RFC 8259 ¬ß5). Recurses into a
non-subscripted local for the same reason as parseObject.

parseCdata.description:
Internal ‚Äî XML 1.0 ¬ß2.7. CDATA content is not entity-decoded;
`&` and `<` are preserved verbatim. Caller appends `text` to
the element's accumulator.

encodeUtf8.description:
Internal ‚Äî used after numeric character reference decode.
U+0000-007F = 1 byte; U+0080-07FF = 2 bytes;
U+0800-FFFF = 3 bytes; U+10000-10FFFF = 4 bytes.
